"h6", "type": "string", "description": "CryptoChart.label (e.g. \\"Solana\\")"}, {"name": "h7", "type": "string", "description": "CryptoChart.product (e.g. \\"XRP-USD\\")"}, {"name": "h8", "type": "string", "description": "CryptoChart.label (e.g. \\"XRP\\")"}, {"name": "h9", "type": "string", "description": "Section.title (e.g. \\"Market Intelligence\\")"}, {"name": "h10", "type": "string", "description": "Section.description (e.g. \\"Latest research and expert commentary on Bitcoin and the broader crypto market.\\")"}, {"name": "h11", "type": "string", "description": "Text.text (e.g. \\"2025 was a landmark — and volatile — year for crypto. Bitcoin surged to an all-time high above $123,000 in August, powered by record spot ETF inflows of $14.4B, Strategy's continued BTC treasury accumulation, and the U.S. government establishing a strategic Bitcoin reserve under President Trump. An \\"alt season\\" in Q2–Q3 saw ETH, SOL and DeFi tokens outpace BTC. However, a sharp October sell-off driven by rising Treasury yields, macro deleveraging, and over-leveraged positions erased much of the year's gains — leaving BTC down ~6% by year-end, underperforming equities and gold. Regulatory frameworks matured: the EU's MiCA went live, the U.S. Senate passed the GENIUS Act on stablecoins, and private litigation stepped up where government enforcement pulled back. Heading into 2026, on-chain fundamentals are improving, but investor sentiment remains cautious. The next leg will be shaped by DeFi regulation, institutional flows, and whether the four-year halving cycle re-asserts itself.\\")"}, {"name": "h12", "type": "string", "description": "Divider.label (e.g. \\"Sources\\")"}, {"name": "h13", "type": "json", "description": "Table.columns (e.g. [\\"Publication\\",\\"Article / Source\\",\\"URL\\"])"}, {"name": "h14", "type": "json", "description": "Table.rows (e.g. [[\\"Investopedia\\",\\"What to Expect From Bi)"}]	Stack(Heading,Grid(CryptoChart,CryptoChart,CryptoChart,CryptoChart),Se